<div id="math-case-study-quiz">
  <h2>Case Study 1:</h2>
  <p>
    In a senior secondary school, the principal decided to analyze the interaction pattern between teachers and students for better management of academic resources.
    The set of all teachers in the school is denoted by T = {t₁, t₂, t₃, t₄}, and the set of all students in a particular class is denoted by S = {s₁, s₂, s₃, s₄, s₅}.
    A relation R from T to S is defined as (tᵢ, sⱼ) if teacher tᵢ interacts with student sⱼ during the week.
    The following pairs are included in R: (t₁, s₁), (t₁, s₂), (t₂, s₂), (t₂, s₃), (t₃, s₄), (t₄, s₅).
  </p>

  <form id="quizForm">
    <fieldset>
      <legend>1. What is the domain of the relation R?</legend>
      <label><input type="radio" name="q1" value="a"> {t₁, t₂, t₃, t₄}</label><br>
      <label><input type="radio" name="q1" value="b"> {s₁, s₂, s₃, s₄, s₅}</label><br>
      <label><input type="radio" name="q1" value="c"> {t₁, t₂, t₃}</label><br>
      <label><input type="radio" name="q1" value="d"> {s₁, s₂, s₃}</label>
      <p class="solution" style="display:none;">✅ Correct Answer: a — Domain is the set of all teachers that appear in the relation R.</p>
    </fieldset>

    <fieldset>
      <legend>2. What is the range of the relation R?</legend>
      <label><input type="radio" name="q2" value="a"> {t₁, t₂, t₃, t₄}</label><br>
      <label><input type="radio" name="q2" value="b"> {s₁, s₂, s₃, s₄, s₅}</label><br>
      <label><input type="radio" name="q2" value="c"> {s₁, s₂, s₃, s₄, s₅}</label><br>
      <label><input type="radio" name="q2" value="d"> {s₁, s₂, s₃, s₄, s₅, t₁, t₂, t₃, t₄}</label>
      <p class="solution" style="display:none;">✅ Correct Answer: c — Range is the set of all students that are paired in R.</p>
    </fieldset>

    <fieldset>
      <legend>3. Which of the following best describes the codomain of the relation R?</legend>
      <label><input type="radio" name="q3" value="a"> {t₁, t₂, t₃, t₄}</label><br>
      <label><input type="radio" name="q3" value="b"> {s₁, s₂, s₃, s₄, s₅}</label><br>
      <label><input type="radio" name="q3" value="c"> {s₁, s₂, s₃}</label><br>
      <label><input type="radio" name="q3" value="d"> {t₁, t₂, t₃}</label>
      <p class="solution" style="display:none;">✅ Correct Answer: b — Codomain is the full set S = {s₁, s₂, s₃, s₄, s₅}.</p>
    </fieldset>

    <fieldset>
      <legend>4. How many elements are in the relation R?</legend>
      <label><input type="radio" name="q4" value="a"> 4</label><br>
      <label><input type="radio" name="q4" value="b"> 5</label><br>
      <label><input type="radio" name="q4" value="c"> 6</label><br>
      <label><input type="radio" name="q4" value="d"> 7</label>
      <p class="solution" style="display:none;">✅ Correct Answer: c — There are 6 ordered pairs in R.</p>
    </fieldset>

    <fieldset>
      <legend>5. Is the relation R a function from T to S?</legend>
      <label><input type="radio" name="q5" value="a"> Yes</label><br>
      <label><input type="radio" name="q5" value="b"> No</label><br>
      <label><input type="radio" name="q5" value="c"> Cannot be determined</label><br>
      <label><input type="radio" name="q5" value="d"> Only if T has more elements</label>
      <p class="solution" style="display:none;">✅ Correct Answer: b — It's not a function because a teacher (like t₁ or t₂) is related to more than one student.</p>
    </fieldset>

    <button type="button" onclick="checkAnswers()">Submit</button>
  </form>

  <div id="result" style="margin-top:20px; font-weight:bold;"></div>

  <style>
    #math-case-study-quiz {
      font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
      max-width: 800px;
      margin: auto;
      line-height: 1.6;
    }
    fieldset {
      border: 1px solid #ccc;
      padding: 15px;
      margin-bottom: 20px;
    }
    legend {
      font-weight: bold;
    }
    label {
      display: block;
      margin: 5px 0;
    }
    button {
      padding: 10px 20px;
      font-size: 16px;
      cursor: pointer;
      background-color: #0073aa;
      color: white;
      border: none;
      border-radius: 5px;
    }
    button:hover {
      background-color: #005d8f;
    }
    .solution {
      color: green;
      margin-top: 10px;
    }
  </style>

  <script>
    function checkAnswers() {
      const correctAnswers = {
        q1: "a",
        q2: "c",
        q3: "b",
        q4: "c",
        q5: "b"
      };

      let correct = 0;
      let total = Object.keys(correctAnswers).length;

      for (let q in correctAnswers) {
        let selected = document.querySelector('input[name="' + q + '"]:checked');
        if (selected && selected.value === correctAnswers[q]) {
          correct++;
        }
      }

      // Show explanations
      document.querySelectorAll('.solution').forEach(function(p) {
        p.style.display = 'block';
      });

      let incorrect = total - correct;
      let score = (correct * 2);
      let percentage = (score / (total * 2)) * 100;

      document.getElementById("result").innerHTML =
        `Correct Answers: ${correct}<br>` +
        `Incorrect Answers: ${incorrect}<br>` +
        `Score: ${score} / ${total * 2} (${percentage}%)`;
    }
  </script>
</div>
